args:
Add two new hook entries to the hooks object in ~/.claude/settings.json.

The file has already been read. The hooks object currently ends with a "CwdChanged" entry (the last key before the closing brace of "hooks"). Add the following two new entries after "CwdChanged", keeping valid JSON:

1. "PermissionDenied":
```json
"PermissionDenied": [
  {
    "hooks": [
      {
        "type": "command",
        "command": "mkdir -p ~/.claude/logs && echo \"[$(date -Iseconds)] Permission denied: ${TOOL_NAME:-unknown} - ${DENIAL_REASON:-unknown}\" >> ~/.claude/logs/permission-denials.log"
      }
    ]
  }
]
```

2. "FileChanged":
```json
"FileChanged": [
  {
    "hooks": [
      {
        "type": "command",
        "command": "FILE=\"${FILE_PATH:-unknown}\"; if [[ \"$FILE\" == *\"settings.json\"* ]] || [[ \"$FILE\" == *\"CLAUDE.md\"* ]]; then mkdir -p ~/.claude/logs && echo \"[$(date -Iseconds)] Critical file changed: $FILE\" >> ~/.claude/logs/file-changes.log; fi"
      }
    ]
  }
]
```

Insert both after the closing bracket of "CwdChanged" and before the closing brace of the "hooks" object. The result must be valid JSON.
